<h2>Question</h2>
<p>Which source code path is actually used for sensor voting / estimator selection &mdash; <code>VotedSensorsUpdate</code> (in <code>src/modules/sensors/</code>) or <code>EKF2Selector</code> (in <code>src/modules/ekf2/</code>)? Are both compiled? Are both active at runtime?</p>

<h2>Short answer</h2>
<p><strong>Both are compiled into the build and both can run.</strong> They are not competing replacements; they are two voting layers at different stages of the pipeline. Which one&rsquo;s output the flight controller actually consumes is gated at runtime by the <code>SENS_IMU_MODE</code> parameter.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Source locations</h2>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Class</th><th>Source files</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>VotedSensorsUpdate</code></td><td><code>src/modules/sensors/voted_sensors_update.h</code>, <code>voted_sensors_update.cpp</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>EKF2Selector</code></td><td><code>src/modules/ekf2/EKF2Selector.hpp</code>, <code>EKF2Selector.cpp</code></td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p>Both are listed in their respective module <code>CMakeLists.txt</code>. The <code>sensors</code> module is enabled by default (<code>CONFIG_MODULES_SENSORS=y</code>, e.g. <code>boards/px4/sitl/default.px4board:44</code>). The <code>EKF2Selector</code> is built only when <code>CONFIG_EKF2_MULTI_INSTANCE</code> is set in <code>src/modules/ekf2/Kconfig</code> &mdash; that flag is on by default unless the board declares <code>CONSTRAINED_MEMORY</code> / <code>CONSTRAINED_FLASH</code>.</p>

<hr>

<h2>What each one publishes</h2>

<h3>VotedSensorsUpdate (instantiated unconditionally inside the <code>Sensors</code> module)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Directly publishes uORB topics:
    <ul>
      <li><code>sensor_selection</code> &mdash; device IDs of the selected best accel/gyro</li>
      <li><code>sensors_status_imu</code> &mdash; per-instance health, inconsistency metrics, priorities</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Populates the <code>sensor_combined</code> struct; the parent <code>Sensors</code> module publishes it:
    <ul>
      <li><code>src/modules/sensors/sensors.cpp:615</code> &mdash; <code>_voted_sensors_update.sensorsPoll(_sensor_combined)</code></li>
      <li><code>src/modules/sensors/sensors.cpp:620</code> &mdash; <code>_sensor_pub.publish(_sensor_combined)</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Input: per-instance <code>vehicle_imu[0..N]</code> topics produced by <code>VehicleIMU</code> workers.</li>
</ul>

<h3>EKF2Selector (only constructed when <code>_multi_mode == true</code>)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Publishes the canonical &ldquo;fused&rdquo; flight-controller topics:
    <ul>
      <li><code>vehicle_attitude</code></li>
      <li><code>vehicle_local_position</code></li>
      <li><code>vehicle_global_position</code></li>
      <li><code>vehicle_odometry</code></li>
      <li><code>wind</code></li>
      <li><code>estimator_selector_status</code> (selector&rsquo;s own health/metadata)</li>
      <li><code>sensor_selection</code> (re-published with the selected EKF2 instance&rsquo;s sensor IDs)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Subscribes to per-instance estimator outputs from each EKF2 replica:
    <ul>
      <li><code>estimator_attitude[i]</code>, <code>estimator_local_position[i]</code>, <code>estimator_global_position[i]</code>, <code>estimator_odometry[i]</code>, <code>estimator_wind[i]</code>, <code>estimator_status[i]</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Picks the healthiest instance by combined test ratio (velocity / position / height errors) with ~10&nbsp;s hysteresis between switches unless a hard fault is detected.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>The runtime switch: <code>SENS_IMU_MODE</code></h2>
<p>Decided in <code>src/modules/ekf2/EKF2.cpp:453-469</code> (subscription split) and <code>:2651-2663</code> (selector construction gate).</p>

<h3><code>SENS_IMU_MODE = 1</code> &mdash; default, &ldquo;sensors module votes&rdquo;</h3>
<ul>
  <li>A <strong>single</strong> EKF2 instance runs.</li>
  <li>That EKF2 subscribes to <code>sensor_combined</code> (VotedSensorsUpdate&rsquo;s voted output).</li>
  <li><strong>EKF2Selector is NOT instantiated.</strong></li>
  <li>The single EKF2 publishes <code>vehicle_attitude</code> / <code>vehicle_local_position</code> / etc. <strong>directly</strong>.</li>
  <li>VotedSensorsUpdate is the <strong>active voter</strong> on this path.</li>
</ul>

<h3><code>SENS_IMU_MODE = 0</code> &mdash; &ldquo;EKF2 votes&rdquo; (multi-EKF)</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Multiple</strong> EKF2 instances spawn (one per IMU, up to <code>EKF2_MULTI_IMU</code>).</li>
  <li>Each EKF2 instance subscribes directly to its own <code>vehicle_imu[i]</code> &mdash; <strong>bypassing</strong> <code>sensor_combined</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>EKF2Selector IS instantiated</strong> and produces the canonical <code>vehicle_attitude</code> / <code>vehicle_local_position</code> / etc. by arbitrating between EKF2 instance outputs.</li>
  <li>VotedSensorsUpdate still runs and still publishes <code>sensor_combined</code> / <code>sensor_selection</code>, but EKF2 doesn&rsquo;t consume <code>sensor_combined</code> here. Only legacy estimators (<code>attitude_estimator_q</code>, <code>local_position_estimator</code>) and a few non-EKF consumers still use it.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Pipeline diagram</h2>
<pre>                          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
                          │            SENS_IMU_MODE = 1             │
                          │           (sensors module votes)         │
                          │                                          │
  vehicle_imu[0..N] ──►  VotedSensorsUpdate ──► sensor_combined ──► single EKF2 ──► vehicle_attitude
                                                                                    vehicle_local_position
                                                                                    vehicle_global_position
                          └──────────────────────────────────────────┘

                          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
                          │            SENS_IMU_MODE = 0             │
                          │             (multi-EKF mode)             │
                          │                                          │
  vehicle_imu[0]    ──►  EKF2 instance 0  ──► estimator_*[0]  ──┐
  vehicle_imu[1]    ──►  EKF2 instance 1  ──► estimator_*[1]  ──┼──► EKF2Selector ──► vehicle_attitude
  vehicle_imu[2]    ──►  EKF2 instance 2  ──► estimator_*[2]  ──┤                     vehicle_local_position
  vehicle_imu[3]    ──►  EKF2 instance 3  ──► estimator_*[3]  ──┘                     vehicle_global_position
                                                                                      estimator_selector_status
                          └──────────────────────────────────────────┘
</pre>
<p>In both modes, VotedSensorsUpdate is always alive and <code>sensor_combined</code> is always published. The difference is whether the single downstream EKF2 reads it, or whether multiple EKF2 instances read raw <code>vehicle_imu[i]</code> directly and the selector picks the winner.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Critical files (with line numbers)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><code>src/modules/sensors/sensors.cpp:615-620</code> &mdash; <code>sensor_combined</code> populated by VotedSensorsUpdate and published.</li>
  <li><code>src/modules/sensors/voted_sensors_update.{h,cpp}</code> &mdash; VotedSensorsUpdate itself.</li>
  <li><code>src/modules/ekf2/EKF2.cpp:453-469</code> &mdash; subscription split: <code>vehicle_imu</code> (multi) vs <code>sensor_combined</code> (single).</li>
  <li><code>src/modules/ekf2/EKF2.cpp:2651-2663</code> &mdash; <code>EKF2Selector</code> construction gate.</li>
  <li><code>src/modules/ekf2/EKF2Selector.{hpp,cpp}</code> &mdash; EKF2Selector itself.</li>
  <li><code>src/modules/ekf2/Kconfig</code> &mdash; <code>CONFIG_EKF2_MULTI_INSTANCE</code> compile-time gate.</li>
  <li><code>SENS_IMU_MODE</code> &mdash; the runtime mode parameter.</li>
  <li><code>EKF2_MULTI_IMU</code> &mdash; how many EKF2 instances spawn in multi-mode.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>How to verify on a running system or SITL</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Check the parameter:
    <pre>param show SENS_IMU_MODE</pre>
    <code>1</code> &rArr; VotedSensorsUpdate is the active voter feeding a single EKF2.<br>
    <code>0</code> &rArr; EKF2Selector is the arbiter, and multiple EKF2 instances are running.
  </li>
  <li>Watch uORB:
    <pre>uorb top vehicle_attitude sensor_combined estimator_selector_status</pre>
    In <code>SENS_IMU_MODE=0</code> mode <code>estimator_selector_status</code> ticks; in <code>SENS_IMU_MODE=1</code> it is not published at all.
  </li>
  <li>Cross-check <code>EKF2_MULTI_IMU</code> if you expect multiple EKF2 instances and verify the <code>ekf2_status</code> topic has the expected number of instances.</li>
</ol>

